# Build outputs (whatever the eventual patch DLL is deployed straight into the
# game root, not committed -- same convention as the sibling MW32011NCP project)
obj/
Debug/
Release/
*.obj
*.pdb
*.ilk
*.log
*.exp
*.lib
*.dll

# Build outputs for dev-only test/research tools (not shipped, not part of the patch)
tools/*/bin/
tools/*/obj/

# Packet captures / traffic dumps used to research or reproduce a vulnerability --
# may contain real player data (IPs, etc.) even from the researcher's own sessions;
# never meant to be committed. Summarize findings in re_notes/ instead.
*.pcap
*.pcapng

# Third-party reference material (cloned locally for research only), same policy as
# the sibling project -- learn from and independently re-verify, never redistribute
# as part of this repo.
references/

# Extracted MW3 game assets -- Activision's copyrighted game data, never ours to
# redistribute. Same defensive safety net as the sibling project.
zone_dump/
ff_dump/
*.gdt

# Internal-only technical detail (exact vulnerable function addresses, precise
# buffer/offset values, exact fix implementation logic) -- NEVER committed/pushed
# to the public repo before a fix for that specific item has shipped. See
# SECURITY.md's "Redaction policy" and CODE_STANDARDS.md's "Documentation
# Standards" for what belongs here vs. in the public re_notes/ docs.
re_notes/INTERNAL_*.md
re_notes/internal/
